Odion Ighalo scored on his competitive debut as Al Hilal won Al Jazira 6-1 to set up a clash with European champions Chelsea in the semi-final on Wednesday. Abdoulay Diaby put Al Jazira ahead on 14 minutes but Ighalo equalised for Al Hilal nine minutes before the break.   Dele Momodu visits hometown 49 years after to declare…     Lagos did not authorise locking of Catholic Archbishop’s…     Insurance cover for Corps members commences Feb 11 –…   The Nigeria international, who recently linked up with the Asian champions from rivals Al Shabab, was replaced by Andre Carrillo in the 75th minute. Former West Bromwich Albion midfielder Matheus Pereira, Mohamed Kanno, Salem Al Dawsari, Moussa Marega and Carrillo scored the other goals for the Saudi Arabia Professional League champions. Al Hilal will face European champions Chelsea in the semi-final on Wednesday.